                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12727544" author="lilywei" created="Mon, 6 Jul 2009 15:22:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the first attempt to fix this problem. I add a second argument to indicate we don&apos;t want to create a new database. This fixed will be the same for 10.5 and trunk. Note: I did not handle schema.sql and avoid recreate Activity.out or performance.out. The test will reuse data in mailsdb database. So, it can test soft upgrade from various release is working.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12732618" author="lilywei" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2009 18:26:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for Kathey to look at this patch that is first post on Derby-4166. I make the changes for the typo. I also do the diff from the top. And, this change only apply for mailjdbc tests. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12732656" author="kmarsden" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2009 19:12:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Lily. I committed the mailjdbc patch to trunk and 10.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
